  "text": "The sequence of events that I considering, which may be easily changed, are first the painting, then the cleaning, then the moving in of the furniture, then the salting, and use of garlic. Is this sequence as good as any other sequence, or would a different sequence be better for those events? I N R sequence which results in the cleansings is acceptable. It is to be noted that the thresholds are not to be across during the cleansing, since such a stricture upon use of the Lemen may affect your considerations. We make note of this.",
